  <p class="th-hero__eyebrow fade-in">Telehealth</p>
  <h1 class="th-hero__heading fade-in">Get diagnosed by a<br>skin expert.</h1>
  <p class="th-hero__desc fade-in">Not sure what's going on with your skin? Connect with a licensed provider who specializes in Malassezia-related conditions. Video consultations, prescriptions, and treatment plans.</p>
  <a href="#th-conditions" class="th-hero__cta fade-in">See Conditions We Cover</a>
</section>

<!-- ====== CONDITIONS ====== -->
<section class="th-conditions" id="th-conditions">
  <div class="th-conditions__container">
    <p class="th-conditions__eyebrow fade-in">What We Treat</p>
    <h2 class="th-conditions__heading fade-in">Three conditions. One root cause.</h2>

    <div class="th-conditions__grid">
      <div class="th-card fade-in">
        <svg class="th-card__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
          <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/><circle cx="12" cy="5" r="1.5"/><circle cx="17" cy="8" r="1.5"/><circle cx="17" cy="16" r="1.5"/><circle cx="12" cy="19" r="1.5"/><circle cx="7" cy="16" r="1.5"/><circle cx="7" cy="8" r="1.5"/>
        </svg>
        <h3 class="th-card__title">Fungal Acne</h3>
        <p class="th-card__desc">Malassezia folliculitis. Looks like acne but doesn't respond to acne treatments.</p>
        <ul class="th-card__symptoms">
          <li>Uniform small bumps on forehead, chest, or back</li>
          <li>Itchy, especially when sweating</li>
          <li>Doesn't respond to typical acne treatment</li>
          <li>No blackheads or whiteheads</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="th-card fade-in">
        <svg class="th-card__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
          <path d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2z"/><path d="M8 12s1.5 2 4 2 4-2 4-2"/><path d="M9 8.5c0-.28.22-.5.5-.5s.5.22.5.5"/><path d="M14 8.5c0-.28.22-.5.5-.5s.5.22.5.5"/>
        </svg>
        <h3 class="th-card__title">Seborrheic Dermatitis</h3>
        <p class="th-card__desc">Chronic flaking and redness in oil-rich zones. Often misdiagnosed as dry skin.</p>
        <ul class="th-card__symptoms">
          <li>Flaky, scaly patches on scalp, eyebrows, or nose</li>
          <li>Greasy or powdery scale</li>
          <li>Redness that comes and goes</li>
          <li>Worse with stress, weather changes, or certain products</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="th-card fade-in">
        <svg class="th-card__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
          <ellipse cx="12" cy="12" rx="8" ry="10"/><path d="M8 9c1-1 3-1 4 0"/><path d="M12 9c1-1 3-1 4 0"/><path d="M7 15c2 1 4 1 5 0"/><path d="M12 15c2 1 4 1 5 0"/>
        </svg>
        <h3 class="th-card__title">Tinea Versicolor</h3>
        <p class="th-card__desc">Patchy discoloration on the trunk caused by Malassezia overgrowth.</p>
        <ul class="th-card__symptoms">
          <li>Light or dark patches on chest, back, or shoulders</li>
          <li>Fine, powdery scale when scratched</li>
          <li>More visible after sun exposure</li>
          <li>Patches that don't tan evenly</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

